data.title: Ozzy Osbourne Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Ozzy Osbourne with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Has been called "The Godfather of Heavy Metal" for helping to create the music genre with the band Black Sabbath

Bit the head off of a bat (he thought it was rubber) during a performance in Des Moines, IA, and was subsequently hospitalized and given a series of rabies shots

Received a star on Hollywood's Walk of Fame in April 2002

Has stated that his favorite band is the Beatles and his favorite album of all-time is Revolver

In 2010, started penning an advice column for Rolling Stone called "Dr

Ozzy

" The columns became the basis for his 2011 book Trust Me, I'm Dr

Ozzy: Advice from Rock's Ultimate Survivor
